<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795DFF90BEF478DAC9A0FF06" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795DFF91BEF478DACD05F937" blockId="4.[151,1437,464,2001]" box="[197,1397,1743,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BEF478DAC921F937" bold="true" box="[197,337,1743,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BFD478DACA5EF936" box="[485,558,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fuscus</emphasis>
= black, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BCAD78DACA9BF936" box="[668,747,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">ventris</emphasis>
= belly, in reference to the black color of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795DFF90BEF478E3C9A0FF06" blockId="4.[151,1437,464,2001]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1435,152,216]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
Discussion. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BF6478E3CAF3F8D1" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[341,643,1782,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BF6478E3CAF3F8D1" box="[341,643,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Macrostomus fusciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BCA378E0CAA5F8D1" bold="true" box="[658,725,1781,1807]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795DFF91BCA378E0CAA5F8D1" box="[658,725,1781,1807]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BD9378E3CCACF8CE" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[930,1244,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BD9378E3CC21F8D1" box="[930,1105,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BAD878E3CDE5F8D1" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1257,1429,1782,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BAD878E3CDE5F8D1" box="[1257,1429,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BEA67909C8AEF8E8" bold="true" box="[151,222,1820,1846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795DFF91BEA67909C8AEF8E8" box="[151,222,1820,1846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BF2C7909C984F8EB" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[285,500,1820,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BF2C7909C984F8EB" box="[285,500,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BC377909CA3DF8E8" bold="true" box="[518,589,1820,1846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795DFF91BC377909CA3DF8E8" box="[518,589,1820,1846]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
on the basis of the shape of male tergite 8, which is acute distally. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BEA67956C9B8F882" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,456,1859,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BEA67956C9B8F882" box="[151,456,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Macrostomus fusciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the thorax predominantly yellow unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BDEE7956CCFDF882" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[991,1165,1859,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BDEE7956CB87F882" box="[991,1015,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BA397956CCFDF882" box="[1032,1165,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BAF97956CDE4F882" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1224,1428,1859,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BAF97956CDE4F882" box="[1224,1428,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which both have a black thorax. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BC8F797FCB1CF85D" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[702,876,1898,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BC8F797FCB1CF85D" box="[702,876,1898,1923]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which also has a predominantly yellow thorax, in having an entirely black abdomen rather than a yellow or reddish abdomen, and in having one pair of scutellar setae rather than two pairs (rarely one pair in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BD2E79A2CBBEF80E" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[799,974,1975,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BD2E79A2CBBEF80E" box="[799,974,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BAFF79A2CD0DF80E" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1230,1405,1975,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BAFF79A2CD0DF80E" box="[1230,1405,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the posterior cercus and the epandrium with the posterodorsal protuberance distinctly longer than anterodorsal protuberance.
</paragraph>
